Fewer than 50 percent of District 5 students were proficient in English Language Arts in the 2022-23 school year across grades three through eight

District 5 students lagged behind the New York City average percentage of ELA proficiency—measured as a score of three or four on the New York State ELA exam—for all grades tested in the 2022-23 exam.
